        <updateDate>2021-07-09T10:24:19Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Veterans Claim Transparency Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to provide the representative of a veteran with an opportunity to review a proposed determination regarding a claim for compensation or benefits before such determination becomes final. The VA must notify the representative in writing that a proposed determination is ready for review and may not make a final determination until the review period has ended.</p> <p>Under the bill, a representative has up to 48 hours to review the proposed determination. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
